<div class="section_title">Smart City: Internet/Telecommunications Provider</div>
<span class="text">
Smart City is the official provider of Internet/telecommunications assistance at the 2005 International CES, and we’ve made it easy for you to reach them.Smart City service desk hours are the same as the move-in and show hours. On-site locations for assistance with&nbsp;existing or new services&nbsp;include:<BR>
<UL>
<LI><STRONG>LVCC North </STRONG>Hall, N4, front of the Hall </LI>
<LI><STRONG>LVCC Central </STRONG>Hall Concourse, across from C3 [Main Smart City Desk] </LI>
<LI><STRONG>LVCC Central </STRONG>Hall Tunnel, beneath C3 Concourse </LI>
<LI><STRONG>LVCC South </STRONG>Hall, Upper Level (South 4), rear of the Hall </LI>
<LI><STRONG>Innovations Plus</STRONG>, near booths 70,367 and 70,254</LI></UL>
<P>A large amount of the challenges Internet customers at CES experience is due to IP configuration. The Las Vegas Convention Center is a static IP facility, which means customers must manually assign an IP for each computer. Smart City can provide you with instructions for this easy process for Windows 95, 98, 2000, XP and for Macintosh computers.&nbsp; </P><STRONG>Questions?</STRONG> Please call Smart City at (702) 943-6080 or Mary Dworin at <A href="mailto:mdworin@smartcity.com">mdworin@smartcity.com</A>.
</span>
<a name="2162"></a>
<img src="/global_images2005/spacer.gif" alt="" width="100%" height="30" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0"><br>

