    <p><strong>Three Tips To Make Your Four Days a Five-star Experience</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    There are a few things at this point in time I realize: One, you’re busier prepping for CES this month than you’ve likely been all year. And two: A few of the no-bones-about-‘em reminders I’m about to give you also may appear in some shape or form in this newsletter.
<P>But we’re down to the count, and of all the things in the world I want for each exhibitor, it’s for you to have a five-star experience this January in Las Vegas. With a month to go, I’ll save the analogies and allegories and cut to three&nbsp;critical things you need to do or know right now:</P>
<OL type=1>
<LI><A href="/exhibitors/resource_center/badges/default.asp">Register your staff now</A>. I just took a look at exhibitor registration numbers, and it seems this is a chore many of you are leaving to the last minute. Take my sage advice: <EM>Reserving a few minutes to get this off of your to-do list will undoubtedly save valuable time on-site</EM>. We’re trying to make it as easy as possible for you; this year, we’re offering group registration. You can upload a spreadsheet of names rather than registering each person one-by-one. If you register by early December, you still might receive the badges in the mail. Otherwise, you can pick them up on-site. </LI>
<LI>Next up is another marketing must. Now’s the time that the other 120,000 CES folks are starting to pick their short-list of must-see exhibitors. And it should be you. <STRONG>We have pre-show registration lists available for rent </STRONG>for your pre-show marketing efforts. This database can be tailored to fit your specific target market. E-mail Wendy Hudak at <A href="mailto:byb@CE.org">byb@CE.org</A> to learn about this. </LI>
<LI>And although your head is spinning with 2005 CES details, there’s a <EM>very important </EM>packet coming your way that details all you need to know about choosing your 2006 exhibit space. Don’t let this slip to the bottom of your stack; you need this information in January. Look at it now, and pack it with you when you hop your flight to Vegas. If you have any questions about 2006 space selection before January 6, e-mail your account representative. </LI></OL>
<P>Okay—You’ve got&nbsp;three great tasks—and great people to assist you. You should be on your way to a five-star experience. See you soon—during what I hope will be the four best days of your business year.</P>
